      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Minimum wage hikes are a classic economic lever that directly impacts small businesses like yours. Increased labor costs mean you'll have to either raise your prices, which can deter customers, or absorb the cost, which cuts into your profit margins. In a smaller town, this pressure is amplified because you often don't have the economies of scale of a large chain to offset the higher payroll. Therefore, you should anticipate tighter budgets and a need to become more efficient immediately.",
